text:
Box office update: MMFF 2016 earns P373.3 million – Star Cinema Star Cinema's 'Vince & Kath & James' tops the MMFF 2016 box office at P105 million Published 11:59  59   NUMBER ONE. The movie 'Vince & Kath & James' is the overall top grossing film of the Metro Manila Film Festival 2016 according to Star Cinema. Photo shows the cast and director Theodore Borborol during the press conference for the film. Photo by Martin San Diego/Rappler 
MANILA, Philippines – Vince & Kath & James is the overall top grosser for the Metro Manila Film Festival (MMFF) 2016, according to the movie's production company Star Cinema. (READ: MMFF 2016: 5 things to know about 'Vince and Kath and James' ) 
In a post on Star Cinema's official Instagram account, Vince & Kath & James earned P105 million from December 25 to January 3. 
The following are the ticket sales of the other movies in the festival, according to Star Cinema: Die Beautiful – P98 million Ang Babae Sa Septic Tank 2 – P45 million Saving Sally – P27 million Sunday Beauty Queen – P7.8 million Kabisera – P4.3 million
